Class ChainedInstanceFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.datalorax.populace.core.populate.instance.ChainedInstanceFactory

    InstanceFactory

    public final class ChainedInstanceFactory
extends java.lang.Object
implements InstanceFactory
    Instance factory that chains to other factories together. The second factory will only be called should the first return null.

      • createInstance

        public <T> T createInstance(java.lang.Class<? extends T> rawType,
                            java.lang.Object parent,
                            InstanceFactories instanceFactories)
        Description copied from interface: InstanceFactory
        Create a new instance of rawType. If the factory does not support the type it will return null. If an error occurred while attempting to create an instance it will through a PopulatorException. Otherwise the call will return a new instance.
        Specified by:
        createInstance in interface InstanceFactory
        Type Parameters:
        T - the type to create
        Parameters:
        rawType - the type to create
        parent - the parent instance, which is needed to create inner class instances. Can be null.
        instanceFactories - the set of instance factories defined in the system
        Returns:
        a new instance or null if the type is not supported by the factory.
